Peel and finely chop 1⁄2 clove of garlic and leave the remaining half untouched. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1}(chopped into quarters). Chop the very top and bottom from the @courgette{1}(sliced in half lengthways) and slice in half lengthways again into 5 lengths and then dice into 2cm cubes.

Pre-heat your #grill{} to high heat and heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a pan on medium heat. Add only the @garlic{1/2%clove}(finely chopped) and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Add @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, @pepper{pinch} and @?sugar{1/2%tsp} (if you have some). Bubble away on medium-low heat until you have a thick sauce.

Slice your @ciabatta{2} loaves in half and grill on both sides. Once they have browned off rub the half clove of garlic into the flat sides.

The tomato sauce is ready when thickened up. Spread the tomato sauce evenly on all the ciabatta halves. Sprinkle on your courgette cubes and a few cherry tomato quarters (but save some for your salad). Tear the @mozzarella{1} with your fingers and lay across the top.

Drizzle a little @olive oil{} on top of each pizza. Grill on high heat until the cheese has melted and everything is well browned.

Meanwhile mix the @wild rocket{1/2%bunch} and remaining cherry tomatoes with @olive oil{2%tsp}. Tear in a few leaves of @basil{3}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Take the pizzas from under the grill, sprinkle over the remaining @smoked paprika{} and tear on some basil leaves. Serve with your rocket side salad.